A little story time - I know I haven't been posting much since the new year , my uncle passed suddenly,  and I flew back to Memphis, January 1st ...
But my uncle Ernest was my Aunt Evelyn's best friend, not just her brother. It was very difficult to see my favorite Aunt so upset..Couple days after the funeral,  I was about to film myself,  but my aunt perked up when she heard this song-'she said " I love marching banks " and it made her smile so I asked if she would do this with me and she said yes! 
I am grateful that this brought her a moment of joy & my cousin Richard showed up right on time to film 🎥, 
#rip uncle Ernest 🙏🏼 I will always be around to lift your sisters spirit when I can. . #weloveyou #lifeisprecious #familyiseverything ❤️

Reposted from @theajzone The great Dr. Martin Luther King graduated from high school at 15, finished Morehouse College at 19, led the Montgomery bus boycott at 26 and won the Nobel Peace Prize at 35. I have been sadden all day to hear about the death of the great #mauricehines .. a lot of people are not aware how instrumental he was to my career start in my days as a musical theatre performer in NYC ..
I traveled the world in his musical productions as part of the dancers and chorus .  From #satchmo musical about Louis Armstrong to my ONE #broadway
credit  a tap dancing fulled show - called "OH-Kay"
